  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following statements about the series <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the sum, from n equals 1, to infinity, of the fraction with numerator open parenthesis, negative 1, close parenthesis, to the n power, times n, and denominator n squared plus 1, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the sum, from n equals 1, to infinity, of the fraction with numerator open parenthesis, negative 1, close parenthesis, to the n power, times n, and denominator n squared plus 1, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mrow><munderover><mrow><mo>∑</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>∞</mi></mrow></munderover><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mstyle></mrow></math></span></span> is true?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
